  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593.32 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-34B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+25.8B), dealers are likely aggressively buying this dip as spot trades near the largest amplifying level. The massive GEX surge event and -491.6% 5-min change indicates heavy option flow just hit, creating this volatile setup where dealers will amplify any directional move. Watch 6590 as the critical pivot—below this level, dealer buying accelerates into the 6580/6585 negative gamma cluster, while a push above 6605 flips dealers to selling mode and could cap upside momentum.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings with strong bounces off 6590 but heavy resistance near 6605.",
